          "body": "The most theologically precise moment in Joshua 3 is 3:15: 'the feet of the priests carrying the ark were dipped in the edge of the water.' The miracle does not precede the step; the step precedes the miracle. God had announced exactly what would happen (3:13) — 'when the soles of the feet of the priests rest in the waters of the Jordan, the waters will be cut off.' The announcement does not eliminate the requirement of obedience; it intensifies it. The priests must step into a flood-stage river trusting a promise. This is the pattern the entire book of Joshua will embody: Jericho's walls fall after seven days of marching (ch. 6), Ai is defeated after strategic obedience (ch. 8), the sun stands still in response to Joshua's prayer of faith (ch. 10). Howard Hendricks observed that the verbs of faith in Scripture are almost always prior to the evidences of faith. Joshua 3 is the paradigm case."
